## Standards

- Australian English throughout: colour, behaviour, organisation, initialise, licence (noun), defence, analyse, catalogue
- Never use em dashes; use commas, semicolons, colons, or full stops
- Fail fast and loud; explicit error handling, no silent swallowing
- OWASP top 10 awareness; no command injection, XSS, SQL injection
- Clean code: max 3 levels of nesting, max 40-line functions, DRY and SOLID
- No dead code, no commented-out code, no TODO comments without linked issues
- Tests are mandatory; run tests before committing; test names describe behaviour
- Inline comments only where logic is not self-evident; document the "why"
